SUMMARY:5K for Foster Kids
LOCATION:4810 N Himes Ave Tampa \, FL 33614 United States
DESCRIPTION:On May 30\, 2026\, the community will gather at Al Lopez Park 
 in Tampa for the 5K for Foster Kids\, a purposeful event dedicated to supp
 orting some of the most vulnerable members of the community. This morning 
 run serves as a vital fundraiser for the Childrens Network of Hillsborough
  County\\\; an organization committed to improving the lives of at-risk ch
 ildren and families through compassionate care and essential services. Par
 ticipants have the opportunity to transform their miles into meaningful ch
 ange\, with all proceeds directly benefiting programs that provide stabili
 ty and hope for children in the dependency system. The race itself is a pr
 ofessionally timed 5K managed by Victory Sports\, ensuring a high-quality 
 experience for both competitive runners and casual walkers. The course tak
 es full advantage of the scenic\, shaded paths within Al Lopez Park\, offe
 ring a beautiful backdrop for a Saturday morning of fitness and philanthro
 py. With chip timing in place\, every participant will receive an accurate
  assessment of their performance as they cross the finish line\, making it
  a great event for those looking to set a personal record or simply enjoy 
 a healthy outing for a great cause. To celebrate the efforts of the partic
 ipants\, an awards ceremony will follow the completion of the race. Recogn
 ition will be given to the top three overall male and female finishers\, a
 s well as the top three performers in various age groups\, ensuring that r
 unners of all stages of life have a chance to be honored for their achieve
 ment. Whether you are aiming for a podium finish or participating to show 
 your support for foster care awareness\, the 5K for Foster Kids promises a
  morning of community spirit\, athleticism\, and heartfelt impact. \n\nPer
 malink: https://www.tampa.gov/node/190291
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.tampa.gov/node/190291
END:VEVENT
